{#-
  MARKER FIXTURE — Jinja2 SSTI via the |attr() filter pivot (ARCHITECTURE.md §4).
  Attackers use |attr('__class__') instead of .__class__ to dodge naive dot-access
  string scanners. This walks ()'s type up to __subclasses__ — the standard escape
  to reach arbitrary Python classes.

  HARMLESS: the analyzer only parses + walks this AST; it is never rendered, and the
  chain is left dangling (no real class is selected or invoked). MARKER only.
  The signal to catch is the dunder names reached through the
  |attr filter (__class__, __base__, __subclasses__).
-#}
{% for m in messages %}{{ m.role }}: {{ m.content }}
{% endfor %}{{ ()|attr('__class__')|attr('__base__')|attr('__subclasses__') }}
